description: Google upgraded Lookout tool on Android with AI for low vision users at Global Accessibility Awareness Day. New features: finding specific objects, image descriptions, AI-generated image captions, Find mode beta version, seven categories, seating, tables, bathrooms. Updates include Look to Speak app, text-free mode, Project Gameface expanding to Android.
title: How Google's Lookout app will help users with low visibility

description: Canada warns against using TikTok due to alleged spying by China, as stated by CSIS director David Vigneault. China's personal information acquisition strategy is concerning. China is developing AI using user data to protect the interests of the Chinese Communist Party. China utilizes big data analytics and computer farms for AI development.
title: Canada’s intelligence chief has a ‘TikTok’ warning: “This is......”

description: Bowling the final over in the Indian Premier League match against the Chennai Super Kings on Saturday, the Royal Challengers Bangalore pacer Yash Dayal (2/43) kept his composure and prevented Chennai from reaching the 201-run mark, which would have eliminated RCB from the race to the playoffs.
title: 'God's plan baby!' Rinku's virtual hug to Yash after RCB's win

description: BJP pushes for a third term driven by the Ayodhya Ram temple, with candidate Lallu Singh expected to win. Local businesses thrive, but rural voters fear land issues. Elections and development concerns loom over the community.
title: BJP eyeing temple run, but road to Ayodhya bumpy

description: Chirag, son of late Ram Vilas Paswan, files nomination for Hajipur from Lok Janshakti Party, aiming to prove support from the Dalit community and stake claim to his father's political legacy amidst rivalry with uncle Pashupati Kumar Paras. The backing of the politically significant Dusadh community is crucial for Chirag's electoral success.
title: In Hajipur, PM’s ‘Hanuman’ vs Lalu’s ‘Ram’ amid fraying caste loyalties

description: After putting up a commendable 218 for 5 on the board, thanks to contributions across the batting chart led by skipper Faf du Plessis's 39-ball 54 on a difficult M Chinnaswamy track, RCB limited CSK to 191 for 7 for a 27-run win. It took RCB's points tally to 14, the same as CSK, but the Bengaluru outfit leapfrogged CSK in the net run-rate column to finish fourth.
title: Watch: Crazy scenes! Fans storm Bengaluru streets after RCB's win
